==English==

===Etymology===
From the Italian phrase ''[[fare fiasco]]'' literally meaning 'make a bottle', used in Italian theatre to mean 'failure in a performance'.

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]:/fiæskoʊ/

===Noun===
'''fiasco'''
# A [[ludicrous]] or humiliating [[failure]].

